children.text: There are areas where the double top plate has an unsupported join where there is a load point above.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 1684 Residential Timber-Framed Construction, Clause 2.4 requires that
‘Where joints occur in either top plate between studs, and where rafter or truss bears onto top plates, additional blocking shall be provided’ .
This area must have additional support placed between the studs to support the load.
